summary: 'Having your personal site built on a framework that is growing at a rapid pace like Next.js, comes with a cost...'
---

When you're building a GraphQL API(Application Programming Interface) you usually start by describing how the client will interact with your API
by writting the schema in GraphQL SDL(Schema Definition Language) and then writting resolvers to resolve the schema. the frustration come when you're using a typed language like typescript
